node.text: In our last episodes covering voting in the 2020 election, our guests came through and dropped knowledge on how we can work together to bring positive change to our communities. Now hear from them on how we need to continue to push to make a difference beyond the election.

node.text: This week on Jordan Real Talk, @AngelaRye and @Baratunde are joined by activist @mspackyetti and Super Bowl Champion @mathieu_era to talk about the importance of continued action and engagement beyond this year’s election.

node.text:
This week on Jordan Real Talk, @AngelaRye, @Baratunde, and guests @hfelton8711 and @MrDavidJohns discuss educational inequality, the issues of school funding, and the importance of Black educators. 

Dr. Felton and David Johns take a deeper dive into how to get involved with education reform, and why local elections are so critical to supporting the educational needs of their community.

node.title: EPISODE 3: HOW TO REFORM OUR EDUCATION SYSTEM

In this week’s episode of Jordan Real Talk, @FatJoe and @Baratunde sit down with host @AngelaRye to discuss the criminal justice system and why reform needs to take place now.

Fat Joe and Baratunde go over the movement to restore voting rights for the incarcerated & formerly incarcerated, and the topics of defunding, and reallocating resources for the community.

node.title: EPISODE 2: IMPACT OF LAW & POLICY REFORM

For this week’s episode of Jordan Real Talk, @CP3 and @Baratunde sit down with host @AngelaRye to discuss a topic that is top of everyone’s mind, voting. 

Chris and Baratunde go over the basics of voting and it’s impact when it comes to local elections, the barriers many voters face today, and the power of the Black vote.

Airing October 7, Jordan Real Talk, Jordan Brand’s new content series, will highlight key issues facing the Black Community and how to drive actionable solutions.

Hosted by social commentator Angela Rye, Jordan Real Talk provides a platform for education and action through conversations featuring Jordan family athletes and influencers, journalists, social justice experts and community activists.

Head to our story to subscribe for the latest episodes.

@naacp_ldf @blackvotersmtr

node.text: The German sneaker culture hub shows us how they built up their brand, and how they’ve built up their team to expand the boundaries of sportswear and sneaker culture. #JUMPMAN

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jordan on August 13, 2021 tagging @jaeecan. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Unapologetically fresh.
We know our WNBA family is elite on the court, but their fits off the court are on a different level. Expressing themselves through their apparel, get a glimpse into the personalities of these high-fashion hoop stars in this week’s #InMyJs.

“My grandmother on my dad’s side gifted me gold and jade bangles that she’d had for 20 years before that. My grandmother on my mom’s side also gifted me her jade bangles. Those were my first pieces of jewelry.”
We spoke with @AlealiMay about her latest Jordan collab, inspired by her Black and Filipina family roots and the precious gifts passed down to her.
Read more at the link in our bio.

@Alealimay can’t miss. Her latest collab is dropping and our Jordan community is here for it. The AJ14’s got a makeover and it resulted in some stunning looks in this week’s #InMyJs.

node.text:
“It feels exclusive. To be part of this Family, to be part of Jumpman, to be associated with MJ himself — it’s elite. I’m excited to be the only quarterback, the only Dallas Cowboy.”
Jordan Brand is thrilled to add @_4dak to the Family. He’s put in the work to make his comeback and we are excited to be a part of his new chapter. 
Read more about the star QB joining our Fam, being an ultimate competitor, and mental health at the link in our bio.

node.text:
In your element.
Destiny feels right at home in the studio as @Miguel stops by to talk with her about how she expresses herself through music. Tapping her feet to the vocals or stomping on the bass drum, Destiny stays vibing in her Jordan Delta 2s.
Watch the full episode in the Nike App.

@Mac10 is a father before anything else. With the new school year coming up, he keeps his sons confident by reminding them of the things that make them great.
Watch the full video of Mike’s family at the link in our bio.
